---
import CTAButton from "./CTAButton.astro";
---

<section class="stack">
  <div>
    <p class="kicker">Apply / next steps</p>
    <h2 class="heading-lg mt-2">Move from interest to a concrete plan</h2>
    <p class="lede mt-4">
      When CSPB looks like a possible fit, the next step is to compare your background and goals with the official admissions requirements, deadlines, cost information, and advising guidance.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="auto-grid">
    <article class="card card-pad">
      <p class="kicker">First</p>
      <h3 class="heading-md mt-2">Confirm admissions requirements</h3>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-neutral-600">
        Review degree requirements, prerequisite expectations, application materials, deadlines, and any official policy language before making decisions.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-5">
        <CTAButton href="admissions" label="Official admissions page" variant="dark" />
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="card card-pad">
      <p class="kicker">Then</p>
      <h3 class="heading-md mt-2">Review cost and timing</h3>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-neutral-600">
        Check current tuition, fees, course availability, and application timing. These details can change and should be confirmed on official CU Boulder pages.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-5">
        <CTAButton href="tuition" label="Official cost page" variant="dark" />
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="card card-pad">
      <p class="kicker">When needed</p>
      <h3 class="heading-md mt-2">Talk with advising</h3>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-neutral-600">
        Advising is especially useful if you are comparing CSPB with another program, thinking about transfer credit, planning around work, or considering graduate options later.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-5">
        <CTAButton href="scheduleAppointment" label="Contact advising" variant="dark" />
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="card card-pad">
  <div class="grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-[1.2fr_0.8fr] lg:items-start">
    <div>
      <p class="kicker">Accelerated master’s options</p>
      <h2 class="heading-lg mt-2">A later planning topic for eligible students</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-6 text-neutral-600">
        Some eligible CSPB students may be able to begin graduate coursework before completing the BS in Applied Computer Science. These post-baccalaureate accelerated master’s options have separate admissions requirements and require careful planning.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-6 text-neutral-600">
        Students should note that some graduate work is expected to be completed on the Boulder campus. For that reason, these options are most relevant to students who are able to meet any in-person requirements. Students should discuss eligibility, timing, financial implications, and relocation considerations with an advisor.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-[1.25rem] bg-neutral-950 p-5 text-white">
      <p class="text-4xl font-black text-[#cfb87c]">4</p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm font-bold leading-6 text-white/80">
        PBAM options are listed for eligible post-bacc students
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="stack">
  <div>
    <p class="kicker">Listed PBAM options</p>
    <h2 class="heading-lg mt-2">Programs to discuss with advising</h2>
  </div>

  <div class="auto-grid">
    <article class="card card-pad">
      <h3 class="heading-md">MS in Computer Science</h3>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-neutral-600">
        A graduate option for eligible students who want to continue into computer science after the BS in Applied Computer Science.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="card card-pad">
      <h3 class="heading-md">MS in Data Science</h3>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-neutral-600">
        A graduate option for eligible students interested in data-focused computing and analytics.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="card card-pad">
      <h3 class="heading-md">MS in CLASIC</h3>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-neutral-600">
        A graduate option connected to computational linguistics, analytics, search, and informatics.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="card card-pad">
      <h3 class="heading-md">MS in Network Engineering</h3>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-neutral-600">
        A graduate option for eligible students interested in network engineering.
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="card card-pad border-l-4 border-l-[#cfb87c]">
  <p class="kicker">Important note</p>
  <h2 class="heading-md mt-2">Use official requirements for decisions</h2>
  <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-neutral-600">
    The accelerated master’s information here is an orientation only. Eligibility, GPA thresholds, prerequisite courses, application timing, financial impacts, and campus expectations should be confirmed with official CU Boulder sources and advising.
  </p>
</section>
